// C2: Acting Components
instance HeatbedActuator : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Primary heating element within the thermal incubator responsible for maintaining or altering internal temperature through controlled electrical resistance."
]

instance IncubatorFan : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Integrated fan system designed to ensure uniform heat distribution within the insulated chamber of the thermal incubator."
]

// C3: Physical sensing components
instance HotZoneTemperatureSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "DS18S20 high-precision 1-Wire digital thermometer positioned in the hottest operational zone of the thermal incubator with ±0.5°C accuracy over -55°C to +125°C range."
    DTDFVocab:producedData HotZoneTemperatureDataTransmitted
]

instance ColdZoneTemperatureSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "DS18S20 high-precision 1-Wire digital thermometer positioned in the coldest operational zone of the thermal incubator with ±0.5°C accuracy over -55°C to +125°C range."
    DTDFVocab:producedData ColdZoneTemperatureDataTransmitted
]

instance AmbientTemperatureSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "DS18S20 high-precision 1-Wire digital thermometer deployed externally to monitor ambient environmental conditions with ±0.5°C accuracy over -55°C to +125°C range."
    DTDFVocab:producedData AmbientTemperatureDataTransmitted
]

// C4: Physical-to-virtual interaction
instance HotZoneTemperatureDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom HotZoneTemperatureSensor
]

instance ColdZoneTemperatureDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom ColdZoneTemperatureSensor
]

instance AmbientTemperatureDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom AmbientTemperatureSensor
]

instance SensorDataTransmissionProtocol : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Safe protocol implemented in the driver layer for reliable transmission of sensor data via 1-Wire bus to RabbitMQ server."
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom HotZoneTemperatureDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom ColdZoneTemperatureDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom AmbientTemperatureDataTransmitted
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance ThermalIncubatorGeometryModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "CAD-based geometric model capturing physical dimensions, shapes, and structural properties of the thermal incubator including chassis and internal components."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo IncubatorGeometryProcessingEnabler
]

instance ThermalBehaviorModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Dynamic simulation model described by differential equations analyzing thermal forces, movement, and system dynamics under operating conditions."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo ThermalSimulationEnabler
]

instance EnvironmentalInteractionModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Physics-based analytical model simulating interactions between the Physical Twin and its cyber/physical environment including environmental factors."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo EnvironmentalSimulationEnabler
]

instance RealTimeTemperatureData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Temporal data stream of high-resolution (12-bit) temperature readings collected in real-time from DS18S20 sensors at configurable adaptive sampling frequency."
    DTDFVocab:fromData SensorDataTransmissionProtocol
    DTDFVocab:inputTo CalibrationAlgorithmEnabler
    DTDFVocab:inputTo FaultDetectionEnabler
]

instance HistoricalTemperatureData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Historical dataset containing temperature readings for trend analysis, performance benchmarking, and predictive maintenance applications."
    DTDFVocab:fromData SensorDataTransmissionProtocol
    DTDFVocab:inputTo PerformanceAnalysisEnabler
]

instance CalibratedModelParameters : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Dynamic set of model parameters (e.g., heatbed efficiency, fan performance) continuously updated through calibration algorithms using real-time sensor data."
    DTDFVocab:fromData RealTimeTemperatureData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo OptimizationEnabler
    DTDFVocab:inputTo PredictiveAnalysisEnabler
]

// C11: Enablers
instance RaspberryPiController : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Raspberry Pi 4 Model B serving as embedded controller interfacing with DS18S20 sensors via 1-Wire GPIO interface and managing heatbed/fan actuators."
    DTDFVocab:enables SensorDataCollectionService
    DTDFVocab:enables ModelCalibrationService
]

instance RabbitMQMessageBroker : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Open-source RabbitMQ server providing intermediate buffering and reliable routing of sensor data between physical sensors and Digital Twin components."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataIntegrationService
    DTDFVocab:enables FaultDetectionService
]

instance PythonScipyOptimizer : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Python Scipy library implementation for mathematical optimization of control parameters and model calibration using non-linear least squares techniques."
    DTDFVocab:enables ParameterOptimizationService
    DTDFVocab:enables PredictiveAnalysisService
]

instance CalibrationAlgorithmEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Embedded Python scripts implementing dynamic calibration algorithms that adjust model parameters (e.g., heatbed efficiency) using real-time sensor data."
    DTDFVocab:enables ModelCalibrationService
]

instance ThermalSimulationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Model-driven simulation engine executing differential equation-based thermal models to reproduce and predict Physical Twin behavior."
    DTDFVocab:enables PredictiveBehaviorAnalysisService
]

instance IncubatorGeometryProcessingEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Geometric processing engine analyzing CAD models to validate physical dimensions and structural integrity of the thermal incubator."
    DTDFVocab:enables DesignValidationService
]

instance FaultDetectionEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "State estimator algorithms comparing sensor data against model expectations to identify anomalies like sensor drift or overheating conditions."
    DTDFVocab:enables FaultDetectionService
]

instance PerformanceAnalysisEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Time-series analysis engine processing historical data for trend analysis, performance benchmarking, and predictive maintenance recommendations."
    DTDFVocab:enables PredictiveMaintenanceService
]

instance EnvironmentalSimulationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Physics-based simulation engine modeling interactions between the Physical Twin and its environment including environmental factors."
    DTDFVocab:enables EnvironmentalAnalysisService
]

instance OptimizationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Optimization engine implementing mathematical optimization techniques to find optimal operational parameters for the thermal incubator."
    DTDFVocab:enables OperationalOptimizationService
]

instance PredictiveAnalysisEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Predictive analytics engine analyzing real-time and historical data to forecast system behavior and potential failures."
    DTDFVocab:enables PredictiveAnalysisService
]

// C6: Services
instance RealTimeMonitoringService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Core service providing real-time tracking of Physical Twin's thermal state via sensor data and calibration algorithms to validate model accuracy."
    DTDFVocab:provides ThermalStateInsight
]

instance DynamicModelCalibrationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service dynamically adjusting model parameters (e.g., heatbed efficiency) using Python Scipy optimization to refine predictive accuracy based on Physical Twin data."
    DTDFVocab:provides CalibratedModelParametersData
]

instance FaultDetectionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Algorithmic service monitoring for thermal anomalies including sensor drift and overheating conditions using state estimators."
    DTDFVocab:provides AnomalyDetectionInsight
]

instance OperationalOptimizationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Simulation-driven service optimizing Physical Twin's operational parameters (e.g., temperature setpoints) for enhanced energy efficiency and precision."
    DTDFVocab:provides OptimizationRecommendationAction
]

instance PredictiveBehaviorAnalysisService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service simulating Physical Twin's response to hypothetical scenarios (e.g., sensor failure) using updated models to anticipate deviations."
    DTDFVocab:provides ScenarioAnalysisInsight
]

instance DesignValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service enabling engineers to validate thermal incubator design through geometric and behavioral model simulations."
    DTDFVocab:provides DesignValidationInsight
]

instance RuntimeDiagnosticsService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service providing operators with real-time diagnostics and performance monitoring of the Physical Twin during operation."
    DTDFVocab:provides OperationalStatusInsight
]

instance PredictiveMaintenanceService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service analyzing historical data to predict maintenance needs and recommend proactive actions for the Physical Twin."
    DTDFVocab:provides MaintenanceRecommendationAction
]

instance SensorDataCollectionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service responsible for collecting and preprocessing sensor data from the Physical Twin for further processing."
    DTDFVocab:provides SensorDataInsight
]

instance ModelCalibrationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service implementing calibration algorithms to update model parameters based on real-time sensor data."
    DTDFVocab:provides CalibratedModelParametersData
]

instance DataIntegrationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service integrating data from various sources including sensors and external systems for unified processing."
    DTDFVocab:provides IntegratedDataInsight
]

instance ParameterOptimizationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service optimizing control parameters using mathematical optimization techniques."
    DTDFVocab:provides OptimizationParametersInsight
]

instance PredictiveAnalysisService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service performing predictive analysis on historical and real-time data to forecast system behavior."
    DTDFVocab:provides PredictiveAnalysisInsight
]

instance EnvironmentalAnalysisService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service analyzing environmental interactions affecting the Physical Twin's performance."
    DTDFVocab:provides EnvironmentalAnalysisInsight
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance ThermalStateInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time insight providing current thermal state of the Physical Twin including temperature gradients and calibration accuracy metrics."
]

instance CalibratedModelParametersData : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight containing dynamically updated model parameters reflecting current Physical Twin behavior and environmental conditions."
]

instance AnomalyDetectionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Diagnostic insight identifying potential faults such as sensor drift, overheating, or other thermal anomalies in the Physical Twin."
]

instance OptimizationRecommendationAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Prescriptive action suggesting adjustments to operational parameters (e.g., temperature setpoints) for improved efficiency or precision."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic false
]

instance ScenarioAnalysisInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Predictive insight simulating Physical Twin's response to hypothetical scenarios including sensor failures and environmental changes."
]

instance DesignValidationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Validation insight comparing Physical Twin's performance against design specifications using calibrated models and simulation results."
]

instance OperationalStatusInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Runtime diagnostic insight providing current operational status including performance metrics and potential deviations from optimal conditions."
]

instance MaintenanceRecommendationAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Proactive maintenance recommendation suggesting corrective actions based on predictive analysis of Physical Twin's condition."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic false
]

instance SensorDataInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight providing processed sensor data for further analysis and decision-making."
]

instance IntegratedDataInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight containing integrated data from multiple sources for comprehensive analysis."
]

instance OptimizationParametersInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight providing optimized parameter values for system operation."
]

instance PredictiveAnalysisInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight containing predictive analysis results for system behavior forecasting."
]

instance EnvironmentalAnalysisInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight analyzing environmental factors affecting the Physical Twin's performance."
]

// C18: Environment
instance ThermalIncubatorEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "Controlled environment encompassing the Physical Twin thermal incubator and its immediate cyber/physical surroundings."
    base:contains ThermalIncubatorPhysicalTwin
    base:contains ExternalEnvironment
]

instance ThermalIncubatorPhysicalTwin : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "Physical system consisting of the insulated box, heatbed, fan, and embedded sensors forming the core of the Digital Twin system."
]

instance ExternalEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "Ambient environment containing external factors influencing the thermal incubator's operation including ambient temperature and humidity."
]

// C19: Components
instance HeatbedComponent : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Primary heating element within the thermal incubator responsible for maintaining or altering internal temperature through controlled electrical resistance."
    base:isContainedIn ThermalIncubatorPhysicalTwin
]

instance FanComponent : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Integrated fan system ensuring uniform heat distribution within the insulated chamber of the thermal incubator."
    base:isContainedIn ThermalIncubatorPhysicalTwin
]

instance IncubatorChassis : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Structural component forming the insulated outer shell of the thermal incubator providing thermal isolation and protection."
    base:isContainedIn ThermalIncubatorPhysicalTwin
]

instance SensorInterfaceModule : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Electronic module interfacing DS18S20 sensors with Raspberry Pi via 1-Wire protocol enabling low-latency data acquisition."
    base:isContainedIn ThermalIncubatorPhysicalTwin
]

// Additional required relationships for the environment
instance ThermalIncubatorPhysicalTwin : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:contains HeatbedActuator
    base:contains IncubatorFan
    base:contains HotZoneTemperatureSensor
    base:contains ColdZoneTemperatureSensor
    base:contains AmbientTemperatureSensor
    base:contains HeatbedComponent
    base:contains FanComponent
    base:contains IncubatorChassis
    base:contains SensorInterfaceModule
]

instance ExternalEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:contains AmbientTemperatureSensor
]

instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Control commands from the Digital Twin are transmitted to the Physical Twin via a **Communication Server** (RabbitMQ) to regulate the **fan and heatbed** within the monitored environment. The control logic employs a **bang-bang controller**, a simple on-off control strategy, where commands are binary (e.g., 'activate' or 'deactivate'). Command formats are not explicitly detailed, but the system relies on RabbitMQ’s message-passing model for command dissemination. Validation and authentication mechanisms are not specified beyond the implied safety protocol in the driver layer, which ensures commands are executed without violating operational constraints. Feedback systems are not explicitly described, but the system assumes real-time monitoring of sensor data (temperature) to inform control adjustments. Conflict resolution is not addressed in the provided context."
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system operates with temporal synchronization between the Physical Twin (PT) and its digital counterpart through continuous data collection from sensors over time, as explicitly stated in the document. The system employs calibration algorithms to update models of the Cyber-Physical System (CPS) and environment with the best parameter estimates, implying a real-time or near-real-time temporal granularity for model refinement. However, the document does not specify exact synchronization frequencies (e.g., milliseconds, seconds), latency requirements, or the use of time-series databases for temporal data management. The temporal aspect is implicitly tied to the iterative process of data collection, model calibration, and monitoring for safe/optimal performance, but precise technical specifications (e.g., sampling rates, update intervals) are not provided."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system is structured as a framework integrating **modelling, simulation, monitoring, and optimisation technologies**, as explicitly defined in the document. It comprises three core components:
   1. **Data**: Collected from the Physical Twin (PT) via sensors over time.
   2. **Models**: Representing knowledge of the PT’s cyber and physical aspects, including its environment.
   3. **Algorithms**: Employed to manipulate data and models (e.g., fault detectors, supervisory controllers, state estimators, optimisers).
   The system employs **calibration algorithms** to update models with the best parameter estimates, which inform **monitoring processes** to check for safe/optimal performance. Violations trigger human or algorithmic interventions to modify the Physical Twin. The document does not specify architecture patterns (e.g., service-oriented, microservices) or resource management strategies, but the orchestration is centered on iterative data-model-algorithm feedback loops for real-time decision-making."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The lifecycle of a Digital Twin (DT) system, as implied by the provided document, is structured around three primary phases: **model development**, **integration into the Digital Twin framework**, and **operational monitoring and optimization**. The **development phase** involves creating abstract representations of the Physical Twin (PT) through models (e.g., CAD for geometry, dynamic models for physics-based simulations) to analyze specific aspects like forces, movement, or system dynamics. These models are not discarded post-deployment but are **integrated into the DT framework** during the **integration phase**, where they are combined with real-time data from sensors and algorithms (e.g., calibration algorithms employing non-linear least squares for parameter estimation). The **operational phase** focuses on continuous monitoring via algorithms (e.g., fault detectors, supervisory controllers, state estimators) to ensure safe and optimal performance. Transition management between phases is implicit in the document, emphasizing the **seamless integration of pre-deployment models** into the DT and the **dynamic updating of models** using real-time data to maintain alignment with the PT. Lifecycle governance is not explicitly detailed but implies a **closed-loop feedback system** where human or automated decision-making triggers adjustments to the PT based on DT-generated insights, ensuring iterative refinement of the system’s behavior over time."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "
The Digital Twin (DT) emphasizes **model fidelity** and **validity** through structured methodologies:
- **Fidelity requirements**: Models must accurately represent the PT’s **physics, cyber components, and environmental interactions**, ensuring high-resolution simulations (e.g., differential equations for dynamics, CAD for geometry).
- **Validation and verification (V&V) methods**:
  - **Verification**: Ensures models are implemented correctly (e.g., cross-checking differential equations against known physical laws).
  - **Validation**: Confirms models predict PT behavior accurately (e.g., comparing simulated outputs to real-world sensor data under controlled conditions).
- **Uncertainty sources and quantification**:
  - **Sensor noise**, environmental variability, and model simplifications introduce uncertainty, quantified via statistical analysis or confidence intervals.
  - **Calibration algorithms** iteratively adjust model parameters to minimize uncertainty (e.g., least-squares estimation for parameter tuning).
- **Error detection and correction mechanisms**:
  - **Monitoring algorithms** (e.g., state estimators) flag deviations between simulated and real PT states, triggering corrective actions (e.g., model retraining or sensor recalibration).
  - **Fault detection systems** identify anomalies in sensor data or model outputs, prompting human or automated interventions.
- **Quality assurance processes**:
  - **Continuous validation loops** compare DT predictions with PT telemetry to maintain model accuracy.
  - **Human-in-the-loop validation** ensures critical decisions (e.g., safety violations) are cross-verified by domain experts.
"
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system’s technical connection infrastructure is centered around a **Raspberry Pi 4 Model B**, which integrates **Wi-Fi and Bluetooth** for wireless communication. Sensor data is transmitted via a **1-Wire bus**, a low-power, single-wire protocol optimized for sensor networks. The Raspberry Pi acts as the primary node for data aggregation, interfacing with the RabbitMQ server for message brokering. No explicit network topology (e.g., mesh, star) or bandwidth/latency requirements are mentioned. Reliability mechanisms are not detailed beyond the use of RabbitMQ for message persistence and retries. Security protocols are not explicitly outlined, but the system implies a **safe protocol** in the driver layer to ensure secure communication between the Physical Twin and Digital Twin components."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "
The **deployment infrastructure** for this Digital Twin system is hosted on a **Raspberry Pi 4 Model B**, which implements the controller and message broker (RabbitMQ) locally. RabbitMQ supports **on-premise deployment**, though no mention of cloud or edge deployment is provided. Computational and storage requirements are not specified, but the system is designed for lightweight operation given the Raspberry Pi’s constraints. Scalability mechanisms are not addressed, and no redundancy or high-availability features (e.g., failover clusters) are referenced. The system’s reliability is dependent on the Raspberry Pi’s hardware and RabbitMQ’s basic persistence features, though no explicit fault-tolerant configurations are documented.
"
]

instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "
The Digital Twin (DT) system incorporates **safety-critical monitoring mechanisms** to ensure operational integrity of the Physical Twin (PT). Specifically, the system employs **monitoring algorithms** that continuously assess system performance against predefined safety thresholds, detecting deviations in real-time. These monitors leverage **calibration algorithms** to update models of the Cyber-Physical System (CPS) and its environment, ensuring the best parameter estimates for safe operation. When violations are detected (e.g., unsafe states or suboptimal performance), the system triggers **human-in-the-loop interventions** or automated adjustments to maintain system safety. The low-level driver includes a **safe protocol** designed to keep the device in a stable state, mitigating risks associated with hardware or software failures. However, the document does not specify detailed cybersecurity protocols, access control mechanisms, authentication systems, or broader risk assessment frameworks beyond these operational safeguards."
]